  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "RESTAURANT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Here’s a clear, practical <strong>job scope for a Middle Eastern Restaurant Manager in Singapore</strong> — tailored to the local F&B scene 🇸🇬🌯</p><h3><strong>Operations Management</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee daily restaurant operations to ensure smooth service</p></li><li><p>Ensure food quality, taste consistency, and authentic Middle Eastern presentation</p></li><li><p>Maintain cleanliness, hygiene, and food safety standards (SFA compliance)</p></li><li><p>Manage opening/closing procedures and cash handling</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Staff Management</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Recruit, train, and supervise service and kitchen staff</p></li><li><p>Prepare staff schedules and manage manpower efficiently</p></li><li><p>Ensure staff follow SOPs, grooming, and service standards</p></li><li><p>Handle staff performance, discipline, and motivation</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Customer Service</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Deliver excellent customer experience and handle guest feedback</p></li><li><p>Resolve customer complaints professionally and promptly</p></li><li><p>Build rapport with regular customers and manage special requests</p></li><li><p>Ensure service aligns with Singapore’s service expectations</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Inventory & Cost Control</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Manage inventory, ordering, and stock rotation</p></li><li><p>Control food cost, wastage, and portion consistency</p></li><li><p>Liaise with suppliers for halal ingredients and Middle Eastern products</p></li><li><p>Monitor daily sales, expenses, and profit margins</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Menu & Concept Management</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Assist in menu planning and pricing with owners/chefs</p></li><li><p>Ensure menu aligns with Middle Eastern authenticity and local preferences</p></li><li><p>Coordinate promotions, seasonal menus, and festive offerings (e.g. Ramadan)</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Compliance & Administration</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with MOM, SFA, NEA, and halal certification requirements</p></li><li><p>Prepare sales reports, staff records, and operational reports</p></li><li><p>Handle licenses, inspections, and audits</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Marketing & Business Development</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Support marketing initiatives (delivery platforms, social media, promotions)</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with GrabFood, Foodpanda, Deliveroo, etc.</p></li><li><p>Drive sales growth and improve customer retention</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Skills & Experience Typically Required</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Experience in Middle Eastern or halal restaurants</p></li><li><p>Strong leadership and people management skills</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Arabic/Middle Eastern cuisine (big plus)</p></li><li><p>Ability to work long hours, weekends, and public holidays</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Singapore F&B regulations</p></li></ul><p></p>",
